{"lemma":"حَوارِيُّو","slug":"حَوارِيُّو","root":"ح.#.ر","root_slug":"ح-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَوارِيّ","root":"حور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9463","n9464"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8F%D9%91%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of white bran-less but gluten-full flour of common wheat (Triticum aestivum)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chalk, or chalky rock"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic חִיוָּרָא / ܚܘܪܐ (ḥewwārā, “white”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9463","headword_ar":"حَوَارِىٌّ","root":"Hwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who whitens clothes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments, by washing and beating them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K.) Hence its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAriy~uwna","text_ar":"حَوَارِيُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companions"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apostles"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disciples"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Jesus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because their trade was to do this. (S, M, Msb.) [Or it is so applied from its bearing some one or another of the following significations.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is freed and cleared from every vice, fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has been tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, time after time, and found to be free from vices, faults,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defects;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAra","text_ar":"حَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he returned. ” (Zj, TA.) ―         -b3-  A thing that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsullied"},{"kind":"text","text":": anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsullied, colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who advises,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acts, sincerely, honestly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faithfully:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friend:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assistant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strenuous assistant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assistant of prophets:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular and select friend and assistant of a prophet"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence the pl. is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companions of Mohammad"},{"kind":"text","text":"also. (Zj.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A relation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAriy~apN","text_ar":"حَوَارِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman; (A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawarowarapN","text_ar":"حَوَرْوَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaworaA='u","text_ar":"حَوْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without implying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawarN","text_ar":"حَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eye: (TA:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAriy~aAtN","text_ar":"حَوَارِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or this pl. signifies women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the cities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) so called by the Arabs of the desert because of their whiteness, or fairness, and cleanness: (TA:) or women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear in complexion and skin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of their whiteness, or fairness: (TA:) or women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inhabitants of regions, districts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracts, of cities, towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and of cultivated land"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh and Bd in iii. 45:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of their whiteness, or fairness. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["Sh","TA","S","Msb","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n9464","headword_ar":"حُوَّارَى","root":"Hwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to flour: (A, * K:) such is the best and purest of flour: (K, TA:) and in like manner applied to bread: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whitened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to flour; (S;) and, in this latter sense, to any food. (S, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiydN","text_ar":"سَمِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaw~arN","text_ar":"مُحَوَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}